hello. boy has it been awhile.

EVERYONE must go to a lake. A nice big one. Or the ocean I suppose. Huge expanses of water make me OH so HAPPY. Wish you all could be here though. This kind of scenery makes me feel artistic and brings on thought-provoking conversations and revelations and such. Mostly I think I am just making this up as I go along. But it feels good. I have been swimming 3 to 4 times a day for HOURS upon HOURS. The water here is terrific. Cept' when you swallow it in large gulps. 

I miss you all.

My father is firmly of the oppinion that ignorance is NOT bliss. And DAMN, it would be nice to have such a noble philosophy. Sometimes I would just rather not know. But does that somehow make things easier? Maybe it just means that you will live a relatively predictable and not so disturbing life until those things that you refused to accept and understand come back with vengence. So would you rather take the medicine in small doses, or all AT ONCE? What will be your choice unravelling? 

Shut up elsa.

I have a distinctly numb feeling in my leg right now. I am restless. Anticipating. Random things like the number of dogs in China and the time it takes to cook a pig might be circulating in my brain. I might ask you: did you fold any socks today? How about towels? Is there any room left in you heart for Ben and Jerry? Where do you plan on being at 4:37 this afternoon? It is likely that the hole in your head is a kind of separation anxiety. Who says that pink is the new black. What does that mean anyway? I am going with green, just to be sure. 

9 days.

I am feeling wierdly content. Also, very, very tired. Last night was a 1:15,this morning was an 8:00. These do not go well together. Whoops. Forgot about the manditory Peace Dining Room meeting. 

WOW. DONE WITH SCHOOL. As I left the building Mr. Fox said: "have a great summer, you'll be back before you know it." WELL THAT'S WONDERFUL. My goodness.

ANOTHER wow. It is June. That means...

tehehehehe.

The Keys to Your Heart

You are attracted to obedience and warmth.
In love, you feel the most alive when your lover is creative and never lets you feel bored.
You'd like to your lover to think you are loyal and faithful... that you'll never change.
You would be forced to break up with someone who was ruthless, cold-blooded, and sarcastic.
Your ideal relationship is lasting. You want a relationship that looks to the future... one you can grow with.
Your risk of cheating is zero. You care about society and morality. You would never break a commitment.
You think of marriage as something that will confine you. You are afraid of marriage.
In this moment, you think of love as commitment. Love only works when both people are totally devoted.
What Are The Keys To Your Heart?

Suddenly comes this realization

You find that you're far too clean

Have you ever slept in fields without worrying about
The grass stains

It's a balancing act in oceans of sand
Falling quickly 
Singing softly

Someday you'll wake up and realize that it all passed you by

Afraid of taking risks
afraid of being vulnerable

But maybe, just maybe you cross that line and you'll find
Yeah,it's painful, its unknown, its not always easy...

hello again. 
So I am sitting here in this familiar cream-colored box of a building with beastly white lights and a drone of click click clicking and shhhh-ing and -"excuse me, that would be one person at a computer,one person at a computer. NO, I am not dyslexic, I am simply quite fond of repeating myself until you make your way properly, directly, in a straight, unimaginative line out our door. And please, do not jump over the red-light-beeper, we like to COUNT how many delinquents we kick out the doors. This is MINE I tell you...ALL MINE." I swear these people are Nazis. 

I feel very small here. Very lost. Very insane. I half expect the walls to be padded. 

So it is drisly outside. But nice...a cool fresh interlude. A pleasant intermission in this sweltering hotness. Perhaps I will run. Unless...no, my legs are still painfully reminded of sunday. I don't exactly know what got in to me. I had some complete breakdown, and I was suddenly incredibly angry with myself. I needed to do something. Be something else. So I went exploring in my woods. I took a three hour nap. I blew off my homework. I ran. I walked I sang. I cried. I played piano for the first time in months.(aghhhh that was bad). I decided that Mom is going to teach me how to play guitar. I took a blanket out into our field and lay down in the grass for an hour. I ate dessert for lunch. SO HA. HAHAHAHAHA I SAY. I want to live. I don't want to waste my life away -something that I too often feel is the case. School, mostly is the thing that brings me down. I feel so confined there. I love my friends, even like some of my teachers...but I don't feel inspired often enough. I dwell to much on missing people...well, Collin -and my sister...Peter, my brother of sorts. I want to be a person who I would want to be around if I were someone else. So here goes. TO LIVING SOMETHING REAL.

love,
the salsaselzerelsaelkayourstrulytickles

here comes the sun...it seems like years since it's been here

thinking with meloncholy nostalgia of dancing on my grandpa's feet...
I am afraid of growing older, why from 6 to 7 to 15...to 16, leaving for college...you can hardly wait, for that next DAY, Month, yeAr, Minute to pass - then BANG. It hits you. you are eighty-years-old and you're singing "britney spears greatest hits." that's oldies music? HA GREATEST HITS. you cant put out a "greatest hits" album while wearing a neon-colored torpedo bra, warping the minds of little girls - yeah they mimmick, they'll have their little head set microphone, they'll screech another sad line of BABy HIT mE onE mOre time. No really please do.

but today i saw the picture of a symphonic sunset and i am telling you - im gonna fall right in. thank you. it was beautiful -as are you. HAPPY HAPPY phone call. :)

so the prospect in the sky is grim today. we shall see about tomorrow.
usually...elsa

my uncle jack was teaching in a juvenile detention center - the days assignment was to write a letter to someone. anyone. and it didnt matter what it was about. jack starts handing out the paper when he comes upon this angry guy: "i aint writing no f*ckg letter" he says. jack hands him the paper. " "i hate the f*ckin paper, dont give me no f*ckn paper,  i aint writing no f*ckn letter!" jack hands the guy and pencil- "wait a min, you hate the f*ckin pencil, right?" guy mutters under his breath: 'f*ckn pencil, i hate that f*ckin paper, aint writing that f*ckin letter. so gradually this dies down as jack leaves the guy alone to make his own decision. 5 minutes later, the guy raises his hand and says:
                            How do you spell "darling"?

this is all true...

I keep going round and round on the same old circuit
A wire travels underground to a vacant lot
Where something I can't see interrupts the current
And shrinks the picture down to a tiny dot
And from behind the screen it can look so perfect
But it's not

So here I'm sitting in my car at the same old stoplight
I keep waiting for a change but I don't know what
So red turns into green turning into yellow
But I'm just frozen here on the same old spot
And all I have to do is to press the pedal
But I'm not
No, I'm not

People are tricky, you can't afford to show
Anything risky anything they don't know
The moment you try, you kiss it goodbye

So baby kiss me like a drug like a respirator
And let me fall into the dream of the astronaut
Where I get lost in space that goes on forever
And you make all the rest just an afterthought
And I believe it's you who could make it better
But it's not
No, it's not
No, it's not

i am in seattle. it is beautiful- more than any big city i have been in. i like it when it doesnt rain. the air smells fresh and is filled with spring richness. i walked outside this morning and looked out over the city, barefoot, messy hair, wearing my mom's sweater. i feel content. for the most part. wishing spring break were just a few days longer...

hello.
I feel like crap.
Today I missed (miss*) Collin more than usual. I feel empty and confused. And angry with myself. I know that there are a million things that I should be doing with my life, and that i WAN'T to do, but I can't seem to focus. I am so happy for him to have this experience - indeed it is the chance of a lifetime. But i can't help wanting him to be here at the same time. I know that I need to stand on my own, and in the long run this whole thing will make me a stronger (better? im not sure) person. i just wish i had someone to catch me on the bad days. I appreciate all you wonderful people who try to do this for me...but im afraid there is a spot that can't be filled at the moment. This is only a piece of the whole thing - but a rather big one at the moment. I wish that i could just put it in storage until june.

Note: the radio can be a very bad thing. Sometimes the songs just seems to parallel my life in a all to freakish kind of way. eeek!

until next time...elsa

Thank You everyone for the wonderful valentines and candy... I feel so stupid that I forgot that it was valentines day. Oh well. My blood sugar levels are way over the top. whoohoo.
I love you all...........elsa

hello all...
Today is a friday. A very good day. I am feeling a wave of newexcitingness coming on. There are bad days here and there - and it is a constant struggle to find worth in the PRESENT, but i im getting there. I am in love with the world and the possibility and a certain person in particular...you know who you are. I feel genuinely happy for the most part. I feel like i want to hug everyone i meet. Is this euphoria or sugar intoxication? Maybe both? or the first because of the latter. I dont know - but i will take what i can get, and hope that it will last for a while.
Go me. as mi hermana says -"yay for joy!"

Days are very blurry. Im feeling very sick of school- but whats new. HAhahaha. Painting class is driving me nuts - i feel so hopeless with this art thing...I dont feel like im getting enough direction. Perhaps that is the point. that - and getting over my perfectionism. It is impossible to paint accurately with the stupid metal thingies. Oh well. We are all in it together i guess. except for amanda of course - she seems to know exactly what she is doing, so we all ask her for advice like she is the teacher. yay. its funny kind of. I like the idea that there are no "right" colors that we should be seeing...that its your own interpretation. This way i will have a retort when mrs. Lorentzen tells my that i have all my colors wrong. So yeah. Sorry for the inconsequential rambling.

so i got a very unsuspected phone call the other night from sir collin. i shrieked. Then dad jumped and screamed - "did you win???" "win what???!!" i yelled back. it was all rather silly. i spent about the first 15 minutes in shock for the fact that i was speaking to him. its kinda trippy - that whole thing about New Zealand being in the future...makes my mind hurt.

CANT BELIEVE THAT BOTH MY SPEECH THINGS ARE GOING TO ALL STATE!!!! im very excited, and at the same time disappointed that we must continue practicing. im pretty sure the excitement outweighs the other stuff though. :)

good note: dad's beard going back to normal. i will think about looking at him now.heehee

I have a backache. I'm not so sure I spelled that right, but oh well. I doubt anyone reads this anyway...
 Right now i should be studying for my spanish and vocab quizzes, but i am entirely unmotivated. Its wonderful when you get to that point of no longer REALLY caring. I have so much to do, but its all to easy not to think about it!!! 
Note to self: I enjoy badminton. Funny, because I could not be worse at it, but I am not dreading P.E. quite as much lately. Granted, this is hardly a work out - but i think that is why i like it. not that anyone is really interested, but yeah.

I Really hate it when people have superiority complexes. I am trying to tell myself that this will not happen when i become an upper classman - but perhaps there is something that im missing...maybe you just get to your junior/senior year, and suddenly everyone and everything is annoying, and how could anyone understand because they are all stupid, naive freshmen. Right? maybe this is uncontrollable. I hope not.Im not attacking anyone in particular here, because, of course, I know some fabulous upper classmen. Im just sick of people putting so much stock in AGE. ITS A NUMBER! im sure we all know that some ten year-olds are mature enough to be twenty, and there are twenty year-olds who are stick firmly stuck in there 3rd grade trousers.

ok...so speech went well i guess! We got a one in readers theater (yea!)AND choral reading. Never would have guessed about the latter. Actually i was rather disappointed. I am SICK OF PRACTICING! oh well. will be over soon i guess. 

I have noticed that I forgive people very easily. It is hard for me to stay angry. Darn it! AHHH! This may be a bad thing, i dont know for sure. 
I feel woozy, and i think im getting sick, but perhaps thats because i have been staring and the stupid computer for hours trying to time my "Who am I" paper (for the second time - yea for me, it all disappeared from my disk!) Im not sure sure who i am anymore. it all gets lost in the the crappy guidelines. I really cant write this way!!! 
I miss having noodles at Sam's house. The fact that i dont know where her house is makes things even more difficult. I want it to be summer...I feel like everyone is drifting apart - maybe this is natural, but ahhggg! Doesnt seem like our friends do anything anymore. Maybe its just that the last time we all really did was at Collin and Annee's going away "party." perhaps the sobering reason for the gathering explained our inability to interact. We just watched movies - always the easy solution. HA. It feels like we (I?) have forgotten how to live. Feeling like a robot. grrr
Dont get me wrong. I'm not depressed. I'm too busy to be depressed. It will all soak in eventually, but im not going to rush things.
 and im off like a prom dress (Yea Jazzy!)-elsa
